  "description": "Praxonic worldbuilding is a recursive method of fictional world construction that begins with pressure rather than premise. It is the applied form of [relational worlding](./relational-worlding.md), elaborated through the Praxonic Worldbuilding Guide into a step-by-step process for constructing worlds from unresolved tension.",
